Java 21 is a Long-Term Support (LTS) release (after Java 17), 
and it focuses on improving performance, simplifying code,


1. Virtual Threads (Most Important)

Helps you create thousands of lightweight threads easily.

Simple:
ðŸ‘‰ Runs tasks faster
ðŸ‘‰ Uses very little memory
ðŸ‘‰ Best for high-load apps (APIs, servers)
---------------------------------------------------------

2. Pattern Matching for Switch

Switch can now check types directly.

Example:

switch(obj) {
    case String s -> System.out.println("String value: " + s);
}


ðŸ‘‰ No need of instanceof + casting


--------------------------------------------
4. String Templates (Preview)

New way to format strings.

Old:

"Hello " + name


New:

String msg = STR."Hello \{name}";


ðŸ‘‰ Cleaner and readable.

--------------------------------------
Unnamed Variables (_)

Use _ when variable not required.

Example:

for (int _ : list) { }


ðŸ‘‰ Avoid unused variable warnings.